Description: TPM 2.0 measured EFI boot with automatic LUKS2 root unlock
 Boots Linux directly from UEFI firmware (no intermediate bootloader),
 seals a LUKS2 root passphrase to TPM 2.0 PCR values, and automatically
 unlocks the encrypted root at boot without user interaction when the
 measured boot chain matches the expected state.
 .
 Supports downgrade prevention via a monotonic TPM NV counter, and falls
 back to interactive passphrase entry under any unexpected failure.
 .
 After installation, run emboot-prepare (optional) to check system
 readiness, then emboot-setup to configure the system.
